<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqchronicles.com/guilds/VoD/" target="top">Visions of Destruction</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is looking for new applicants to join our family. Our ultimate goal is to be a seasoned raiding guild. Because that goal involves becoming a guild which can handle any challenge, we do have a few requirements in order to join.<br>
<br>
*You must be level 46 or higher. We are looking for players who are familiar with the game and have made some sort of commitment to it overall. 46 is also the minimum level for most planes and since our weekend raids and events usually take place in the more challenging areas we need our members to be appropriately leveled to attend.<br>
<br>
*We request that you play at least 20 hours a week but more is encouraged and rewarded. Why so much? Because in order to become successful when it comes to raiding we need to learn from one another and know each other as more than just a passing stranger with a guild tag under their name. Friends are more likely to support each other when raids go bad and cheer on one another when things are going great.<br>
<br>
*We request that you maintain an active presence on our guild boards and within guild chat. The boards are the number one source for communication outside of the game and should be treated as a part of the game. It is your responsibility to check them, respond to threads when asked (such as sign up threads), and to ensure that you are aware of the knowledge found there. This also cuts down on prep time for events since the guild boards contain the important information to get everyone there on time and prepared.<br>
<br>
*We request that you attend as many raids as possible and if you are online when a raid is scheduled you are required to be there if you can. We understand that real life comes first and that sometimes things might happen but we also hope that you will want the guild to be successful and as a result will do everything possible to be prepared and on time for each raid that is scheduled if you -can- make it. Understand that we raid primarily on the weekends so if your play time does not include weekends it is not likely that you will be able to attend most of our raids. We do hold a minimum raid requirement a month but that number is still under consideration and changing as we grow.<br>
<br>
We often raid on Friday nights, and Saturday and Sunday during the day and evening. Most of the guild is on Eastern Standard Time but that is likely to change depending on new recruits and their time zones. Epic fights and other fights which require a smaller raid force are also scheduled during the week depending on the amount of people online and prepared to play. Our guild bank is constantly changing and upgrades from our daily adventures are usually given to the guild rather than sold for our own benefit. We do our best to provide our clerics with the gems they need for buffs and others who might need supplies as well. We have even gone as far as helping to fund trade skills in certain cases if the grandmaster in the end can provide a service to the guild.<br>
<br>
Our current goals include perfecting our raiding skills, having a go at some of the classic EQ encounters and planes and gearing up our members to prepare us for tier 1 and above in the planes of power. We are still learning, but in learning together and working as a team our accomplishments far outweigh any material prize we might win on any raid.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time.<br>
Mian Sorrowsoul<br>
